                    </div>
                    <span>The first 3-4 chapters of this bbok are like a standard military uniform issue, and can be found in almost all of Deitel's books on the programming languages. That can be good anc comforting if you are already familiar with their style or if you are new ot programming. It can be painfully mind numbing for anyone with over 1 year's programming experience. <P>The structure of this book is no different from other Deitel books. So if you looking to tread unfamiliar terrain in familiar clothes, this is the book for you. If you want to get better value go look some place else. (I am looking too). Since this is the recommded text for the course, I am stuck with it for now. But personally, this is not gonna be my desk reference copy. Having said that.... the book does provide lots and lots of worked out examples (with logic and typo errors). color scheme printing eases the understanding process, and if you are a beginner in the java arena, stick with this book for now, until you are ready to fly away. and then you dont ever need to look back upon it.</span>
                  
